ction of simulated $r$-II stars is commensurate\nwith observations from the RPA, and the distribution of the predicted [Eu/Fe]\nfor halo $r$-II stars matches that observed. These results demonstrate that RPE\nstars can be valuable probes of the accretion of dwarf galaxies in the early\nstages of their formation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 8 Jun 2022 18:00:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 28 Aug 2022 18:10:22 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 31 Aug 2022 20:35:57 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Tue, 13 Dec 2022 22:36:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-12-15"}
