aints\non whether or not a disk is present, the observation of additional molecular\ntracers, and estimating envelope density will help in accurately determining\nthe cause of the observed snowline position. Plots of the N$_2$H$^+$ and\nHCO$^+$ peak emission radius versus luminosity are provided to compare the\nmodels with observations of deeply embedded protostars aiming to measure the CO\nand H$_2$O snowline locations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 9 Jun 2022 07:21:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-09-14"}
