{"id":"2206.04555","submitter":"Ricardo Alberto Podest\\'a","authors":"Ricardo A. Podest\\'a, Maximiliano G. Vides","title":"Lee metrics on groups","comments":"26 pages, 5 tables","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.GR math.CO math.GT","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  In this work we consider interval metrics on groups; that is, integral\ninvariant metrics whose associated weight functions do not have gaps. We give\nconditions for a group to have and to have not interval metrics. Then we study\nLee metrics on general groups, that is interval metrics having the finest\nunitary symmetric associated partition. These metrics generalize the classic\nLee metric on cyclic groups. In the case that $G$ is a torsion-free group or a\nfinite group of odd order, we prove that $G$ has a Lee metric if and only if\n$G$ is cyclic. Also, if $G$ is a group admitting Lee metrics then $G \\times\n\\mathbb{Z}_2^k$ always have Lee metrics for every $k \\in \\mathbb{N}$. Then, we\nshow that some families of metacyclic groups, such as cyclic, dihedral, and\ndicyclic groups, always have Lee metrics. Finally, we give conditions for\nnon-cyclic groups such that they do not have Lee metrics. We end with tables of\nall groups of order $\\le 31$ indicating which of them have (or have not) Lee\nmetrics and why (not).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 9 Jun 2022 15:07:12 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 27 Feb 2023 14:22:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-28"}
